are Factory\\\" automation in the Entire CLI, based on Dan Shapiro's Five Levels of AI-Assisted Programming framework.\\n\\n## Background: The Five Levels Framework\\n\\nAnalogous to self-driving car levels:\\n\\n| Level | Name | Description |\\n|-------|------|-------------|\\n| 0 | Spicy Autocomplete | Basic tab completion, every character needs human approval |\\n| 2 | AI Pair Programming | Copilot/Cursor level - human still approves everything |\\n| 3 | Human as Manager | AI does the coding, you spend your days reviewing diffs |\\n| 5 | Dark Software Factory | Fully autonomous AI, humans design validation systems |\\n\\n### Level 5 Key Principles\\n\\n1. **Zero code review** - Nobody reviews AI-produced code, ever\\n2. **Proof-oriented development** - Massive investment in automated testing, validation, simulations\\n3. **Human role shifts** - Design validation architectures, not write/review code\\n4. **The code is not the artifact** - The proof that it works is what matters\\n\\nNamed after Fanuc's \\\"Dark Factory\\\" - a robot factory that runs with lights off because robots don't need to see.\\n\\n### Sources\\n\\n- Dan Shapiro: https://www.danshapiro.com/blog/2026/01/the-five-levels-from-spicy-autocomplete-to-the-software-factory/\\n- Simon Willison: https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jan/28/the-five-levels/\\n\\n## Current State\\n\\n**Entire CLI** is a git-integrated session capture system for AI-driven development:\\n- Records AI agent transcripts (Claude Code, Gemini CLI)\\n- Creates checkpoints tied to git commits\\n- Preserves metadata without polluting commit history\\n- Enables rewind/resume of sessions\\n\\n**Current autonomy level**: Level 1 (lightweight automation with human oversight)\\n\\n## Phase 1: Validation Command (Implemented)\\n\\nAdded a hidden `entire validate` command that runs configurable proof checks.\\n\\n### Usage\\n\\n```bash\\nentire validate              # Run all configured proofs\\nentire validate --proof test # Run specific proof types\\nentire validate --json       # JSON output for automation\\n```\\n\\n### Configuration\\n\\nAdd to `.entire/settings.json`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"strategy_options\\\": {\\n    \\\"validation\\\": {\\n      \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n      \\\"proofs\\\": [\\n        {\\\"type\\\": \\\"test\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"mise run test\\\", \\\"required\\\": true},\\n        {\\\"type\\\": \\\"lint\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"mise run lint\\\", \\\"required\\\": true},\\n        {\\\"type\\\": \\\"typecheck\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"go build ./...\\\", \\\"required\\\": true},\\n        {\\\"type\\\": \\\"security\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"gosec ./...\\\", \\\"required\\\": false}\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Files\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/validate.go` - Command implementation\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/validate_test.go` - Test suite (26 tests)\\n\\n## Phase 2: Validation Storage (Proposed)\\n\\nStore validation results alongside checkpoint metadata.\\n\\n### Goals\\n\\n- Every checkpoint includes proof results\\n- Historical record of what passed/failed\\n- Queryable validation history\\n\\n### Implementation Sketch\\n\\n```go\\n// Extend checkpoint metadata\\ntype CheckpointMetadata struct {\\n    // ... existing fields ...\\n    Validation *ValidationResult `json:\\\"validation,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// Store after SaveChanges()\\nfunc (s *Strategy) SaveChanges(ctx, saveCtx) error {\\n    // ... existing logic ...\\n\\n    if validationEnabled {\\n        result := runProofs(...)\\n        saveCtx.Checkpoint.Validation = result\\n    }\\n\\n    // ... continue saving ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Phase 3: Feedback Injection (Proposed)\\n\\nWhen validation fails, write errors for the AI agent to read on next prompt.\\n\\n### Goals\\n\\n- Agent sees failure context without human intervention\\n- Self-correction without human review\\n- Structured error format for easy parsing\\n\\n### Implementation Sketch\\n\\n```go\\n// Write failure context to agent-readable location\\nfunc InjectFeedback(sessionDir string, result *ValidationResult) error {\\n    if result.Passed {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n\\n    feedback := formatFailuresForAgent(result)\\n    return os.WriteFile(\\n        filepath.Join(sessionDir, \\\".entire\\\", \\\"validation-feedback.md\\\"),\\n        []byte(feedback),\\n        0644,\\n    )\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAgent hooks can read this file on `SessionStart` to provide context.\\n\\n## Phase 4: Auto-Fix Loop (Proposed)\\n\\nValidation failure triggers agent retry automatically.\\n\\n### Goals\\n\\n- Automated fix attempts without human intervention\\n- Configurable retry limits\\n- Human escalation only after N failures\\n\\n### Flow\\n\\n```\\nAgent produces code\\n       │\\n       ▼\\n   Checkpoint\\n       │\\n       ▼\\n  Run Proofs ──────► All Pass? ──► Auto-commit\\n       │\\n       ▼ Fail\\n  Inject Feedback\\n       │\\n       ▼\\n  Retry < Max? ──────► No ──► Escalate to Human\\n       │\\n       ▼ Yes\\n  Agent Retries\\n       │\\n       └──────────────────────────────┘\\n```\\n\\n### Configuration\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"strategy_options\\\": {\\n    \\\"validation\\\": {\\n      \\\"auto_fix\\\": {\\n        \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n        \\\"max_retries\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"escalate_on_failure\\\": true\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Phase 5: Autonomous Commit Mode (Proposed)\\n\\nAuto-commit when all proofs pass.\\n\\n### Goals\\n\\n- Zero human review for validated changes\\n- Clean commit messages with proof summary\\n- Full audit trail in metadata\\n\\n### New Strategy: `autonomous`\\n\\n```go\\ntype AutonomousStrategy struct {\\n    base           *ManualCommitStrategy\\n    validation     *ValidationRunner\\n    maxRetries     int\\n    autoCommit     bool\\n    autoPush       bool\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Commit Message Format\\n\\n```\\nfeat: implement user authentication\\n\\nProofs passed:\\n- tests: 142/142 ✓\\n- coverage: 87% (≥80%) ✓\\n- lint: 0 errors ✓\\n- security: 0 vulnerabilities ✓\\n\\nEntire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\nEntire-Autonomous: true\\n```\\n\\n## Phase 6: Metrics & Observability (Proposed)\\n\\nTrack validation outcomes over time.\\n\\n### Metrics to Collect\\n\\n| Metric | Purpose |\\n|--------|---------|\\n| `validation_pass_rate` | How often agent code passes first time |\\n| `fix_loop_iterations` | Average retries before success |\\n| `common_failures` | Most frequent validation failures |\\n| `agent_effectiveness` | Success rate by task type |\\n| `proof_duration` | Time spent validating |\\n\\n### Commands\\n\\n```bash\\nentire metrics               # Show agent effectiveness metrics\\nentire metrics --export csv  # Export for analysis\\n```\\n\\n### Storage\\n\\n```\\n.entire/metrics/\\n├── daily/\\n│   └── 2026-01-31.json\\n└── aggregate.json\\n```\\n\\n## Architecture Overview\\n\\n```\\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n│                     LEVEL 5 ARCHITECTURE                     │\\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\\n│                                                              │\\n│  ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────┐    ┌──────────────────────┐  │\\n│  │  Human   │───▶│   Spec    │───▶│     AI Agent         │  │\\n│  │ Designer │    │  + Proofs │    │  (Claude Code, etc)  │  │\\n│  └──────────┘    └───────────┘    └──────────┬───────────┘  │\\n│       │                                       │              │\\n│       │                                       ▼              │\\n│       │              ┌────────────────────────────────────┐  │\\n│       │              │          Entire CLI                │  │\\n│       │              │  ┌──────────────────────────────┐  │  │\\n│       │              │  │      Checkpoint Created       │  │  │\\n│       │              │  └──────────────┬───────────────┘  │  │\\n│       │              │                 ▼                  │  │\\n│       │              │  ┌──────────────────────────────┐  │  │\\n│       │              │  │    Validation Runner         │  │  │\\n│       │              │  │  ┌────┐ ┌────┐ ┌────┐ ┌───┐  │  │  │\\n│       │              │  │  │Test│ │Lint│ │Type│ │Sec│  │  │  │\\n│       │              │  │  └──┬─┘ └──┬─┘ └──┬─┘ └─┬─┘  │  │  │\\n│       │              │  └────┼──────┼──────┼─────┼────┘  │  │\\n│       │              │       └──────┴──────┴─────┘       │  │\\n│       │              │                 │                  │  │\\n│       │              │         ┌───────┴───────┐          │  │\\n│       │              │         ▼               ▼          │  │\\n│       │              │    ┌─────────┐    ┌──────────┐     │  │\\n│       │              │    │  Pass   │    │   Fail   │     │  │\\n│       │              │    └────┬────┘    └────┬─────┘     │  │\\n│       │              │         │              │           │  │\\n│       │              │         ▼              ▼           │  │\\n│       │              │  ┌───────────┐  ┌────────────┐     │  │\\n│       │              │  │Auto-Commit│  │Feedback to │     │  │\\n│       │              │  │ + Push    │  │   Agent    │─────┼──┤\\n│       │              │  └───────────┘  └────────────┘     │  │\\n│       │              └────────────────────────────────────┘  │\\n│       │                                                      │\\n│       │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\\n│       └─▶│              Observability                     │   │\\n│          │  • Validation pass rate                        │   │\\n│          │  • Fix loop iterations                         │   │\\n│          │  • Common failure patterns                     │   │\\n│          │  • Agent effectiveness metrics                 │   │\\n│          └───────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\\n│                                                              │\\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n```\\n\\n## Session Handoff Notes\\n\\n### Branch\\n\\n`claude/review-ai-levels-Zx5Ww` - already pushed with Phase 1 implementation\\n\\n### Tests to Run\\n\\nThe previous session had Go toolchain issues (sandbox blocked `storage.googleapis.com`). Please run:\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run test\\nmise run lint\\n```\\n\\n### Files Changed\\n\\n```\\ncmd/entire/cli/validate.go      # New - validation command\\ncmd/entire/cli/validate_test.go # New - 26 test cases\\ncmd/entire/cli/root.go          # Modified - registered command\\ndocs/dark-software-factory-roadmap.md  # New - this file\\n```\\n\\n### Key Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **Hidden command** - `entire validate` is hidden (`Hidden: true`) as experimental\\n2. **Config location** - Validation config stored in `strategy_options.validation` to avoid schema changes\\n3. **Proof model** - Each proof is a shell command with type, required flag, and timeout\\n4. **JSON output** - `--json` flag enables automation/scripting\\n5. **Optional proofs** - Proofs can be marked `required: false` to allow advisory checks\\n\",\"numLines\":337,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":337}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"53801cc8-115a-4559-b3b8-eda09a47e762\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d719ff69-0229-4764-9571-b077f21f8dd1\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"10f317d4-f0f8-49d0-9cd3-f42bc0e361c7\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"cli_experiments\",\"slug\":\"tidy-wishing-mochi\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01MZsAN68VMNbqJbTrmyt4u7\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I need to check the current state of `root.go` in this repo and see if `LoadEntireSettings` exists here (the old repo used a different function name/location).\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":15690,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":46778,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_